Configuration:
 # Write H2, SqlLite or YAML if you want a database gesture with H2, SqlLite or a simple file
 Database: "H2"


 # Available worlds
 World:
 # If you set on true change whitelist with blacklist
 Blacklist: false
 List:
 - "world"
 - "world_nether"
 - "world_the_end"


 GeneratorInterface:
 InterfaceOpenWith:
 # Interface open click 'LEFT_CLICK_BLOCK', 'RIGHT_CLICK_BLOCK' or ''
 Click: 'RIGHT_CLICK_BLOCK'
 # If you want shift + click change to true
 Shift: false
 # Allow the user to open the interface with empty hand
 InterfaceOpenWithEmptyHand: true
 # Allow the user to take items from the interface
 InterfaceItemTake: true
 # Maximum number of Items per Slot, set it to -1 for infinity and what you want display
 MaxItemForSlot: '-1:Unlimited'
 # Allow you to configure the number of slots that can be used in the generator
 InterfaceSlotEnabled: false
 # Enable CubeGenerator size upgrade when reach max level.
 UpgradeSize: false
 # Enable a button that allows you to upgrade the CubeGenerator at the highest level you can purchase
 FastUpgrade: false
 # Enable a type mode of give item (Es. Interface, Inventory, Ground)
 ItemCollecting: 'Interface'


 # Enable CubeGenerator build animation: piece by piece
 BuildAnimation: true


 # Enable CubeGenerator destroy animation: piece by piece
 DestroyAnimation: true


 # If true: only the owner of the CubeGenerator will be able to place this CubeGenerator;
 # If false: whoever places this CubeGenerator becomes the owner
 GeneratorOwnerControl: true


 # Max number of CubeGenerator that a player can place at the same time, set to -1 to disable
 MaxCubeGenerator: -1


 # Do you want the blocks mined by the CubeGenerator to also give XP points?
 ExpGiveFromBlocks: true


 # Do you want when you use an item to break generator blocks it decreases its duration?
 ItemDamage: true


 # Here you can set the appearance of the chest in your hand
 ChestItem:
 Name: '&aCubeGenerator Chest'
 Lore:
 - '&7&oPlace &7the Chest near'
 - '&7the CubeGenerator'


 # Set whether various plugins should be hooked into (I will also check if is enabled).
 Hooks:
 CrazyEnchantments: false
 McMMO: false
 TokenEnchant:
 # Attention A TPS loss may occur!
 Enabled: false
 # If you have problems, you can keep token enchant by disabling the events on generator!
 EnabledEvent: false
 PlotSquared: false
 PlotSquaredOLD: false
 PlotSquaredLegacy: false
 WildStacker: false
 SuperiorSkyblock2: false
 WildTools: false
 ShopGuiPlus: false
 Lands:
 Enabled: false
 # Excluded Lands (names)
 ExcludedLands:
 - "Widerness"
 PlaceholderAPI: false
 AdvancedEnchantments: false
 HolographicDisplays:
 Enabled: false
 # UP to place the hologram above the generator
 # DOWN to place the hologram under the generator
 # CENTERCORNER1 to place the hologram on a corner
 # CENTERCORNER2 to place the hologram on a corner
 # CENTERCORNER3 to place the hologram on a corner
 # CENTERCORNER4 to place the hologram on a corner
 # CENTERUP1 to place the hologram in the center of the high side
 # CENTERUP2 to place the hologram in the center of the high side
 # CENTERUP3 to place the hologram in the center of the high side
 # CENTERUP4 to place the hologram in the center of the high side
 # CENTERDOWN1 to place the hologram in the center of the low side
 # CENTERDOWN2 to place the hologram in the center of the low side
 # CENTERDOWN3 to place the hologram in the center of the low side
 # CENTERDOWN4 to place the hologram in the center of the low side
 Position: 'UP'
 Text:
 - "&a&l{owner}"
 - "&a&l{id}"
 - "&a&l{type}"
 - "&a&l{level}"
 - "&a&lAutoSell Enabled: {autosell}"
 - "&a&lAutoMining Enabled: {automining}"
 WorldEdit: false
 JetsMinions: false
 LitMinions: false
 MiningEconomy:
 Enabled: false
 # Do you want when you use a mining economy pickaxe to break generator blocks it decreases its duration?
 ItemDamage: false
 EcoEnchants: false
 RevEnchants: false
 ItemsAdder: false

 # If ShopGuiPlus is disabled, you will use this price scheme
 Prices:
 COBBLESTONE: 1.0
 STONE: 1.0


 # Generators

 3x3:
 Size: '3x3'
 Name: '&aCubeGenerator &8(&a3x3&8)'
 Type: 'PLAYER_HEAD' # SKULL_ITEM;3 <1.13

# you can use a different coloring by using a hexadecimal. for all messages Ex. &{#FFFF00}(yellow).
# Example for a command: '/cg &{#FFFF00}[size] &{#000000}Allows you to gen a new CubeGenerator.'
Messages:
 Commands:
 Base: '&e /cg &6[size] &7Allows you to get a new CubeGenerator'
 Time: '&e /cg &6<time> <add/set/remove> <autofill/autosell/automining> <value> <playerName> <generatorID> &7Allows you to add,remove and set time for autofill,automining and autosell'
 Slot: '&e /cg &6<slot> <add/set/remove> <value> <playerName> <generatorID> &7Allows you to add,remove and set the number of slot'
 Give: '&e /cg &6<give> <size> <player name> <level> &7Allows you to give the CubeGenerator'
 ExampleGenerator: '&e /cg &6<example> <size> &7Allows you to get a new example of CubeGenerator'
 Chest: '&e /cg &6<chest> <playerName|remove> &7Allows you to give/remove a chest for CubeGenerator'
 CreateSchematic: '&e /cg &6<create> <schematic> <size> &7Allows you to create a schematic of CubeGenerator'
 Reload: '&e /cg &6<reload> &7Allows you to reload the Plugin'
 Select: '&e /cg &6<select> [playerName] &7Allows you to have an overview of the player''s CubeGenerators'
 Remove: '&e /cg &6<remove> &7Allows you to remove a CubeGenerator'
 Restore: '&e /cg &6<restore> [file] &7Allows you to restore a H2Database from backup file or see the list of backup files'
 Members:
 Add: '&e /cg &6<member> <add> <generatorID> <playerName> &7Send a request at player for add them as member of generator'
 Remove: '&e /cg &6<member> <remove> <generatorID> <playerName> &7Remove a player from generator'
 Accept: '&e /cg &6<member> <accept> &7Accept request to be added as a member of a generator'
 Refuse: '&e /cg &6<member> <refuse> &7Refuse request to be added as a member of a generator'
 Footer: '&7(&7&l(&c&l!&7&l)&7) &9[] optional value, <> required'
